Additional Use Grant:

You may make Production Use of the Licensed Work, provided that:

1. Your use does not include offering the Licensed Work to third parties on a Hosted or Embedded basis as part of a Competitive Offering; and
2. either:
   a. You are not a For-Profit Entity; or
   b. Your Employee Count does not exceed 100.

For purposes of this license:

"Affiliate" means any legal entity that directly or indirectly Controls, is Controlled by, or is under Common Control with a person or entity.

"Common Control" means that two or more entities are Controlled by the same person or entity.

"Competitive Offering" means a Product that is offered to third parties for a fee or other commercial consideration, including through paid support arrangements, and that significantly overlaps with: (a) the capabilities of Licensor's paid version(s) of the Licensed Work; or (b) if Licensor has not yet made a paid version generally available, the material capabilities of the Licensed Work itself. If Your Product is not a Competitive Offering when You first make it generally available, it will not become a Competitive Offering later solely because Licensor releases a new version of the Licensed Work with additional capabilities. In addition, Products that are not provided for a fee or other commercial consideration are not Competitive Offerings.

"Control" means the direct or indirect power to direct the management or policies of an entity, whether by ownership, voting rights, contract, or otherwise. Ownership or beneficial ownership of fifty percent (50%) or more of the voting interests of an entity will be deemed Control.

"Embedded" means including the source code or executable code from the Licensed Work in a Product. "Embedded" also means packaging a Product in such a way that the Licensed Work must be accessed or downloaded for the Product to operate.

"Employee" means a natural person employed by You or any of Your Affiliates on a full-time, part-time, temporary, or seasonal basis, counted by headcount and not by full-time-equivalent calculation. Employee includes officers and managers who are employees under applicable law. Employee does not include independent contractors, except that, for anti-circumvention purposes, persons supplied by staffing firms or similar arrangements who work substantially full-time for You or any Affiliate for more than ninety (90) consecutive days may be treated as Employees.

"Employee Count" means the highest number of Employees of You and Your Affiliates at any time during the immediately preceding twelve (12) calendar months. If You or any Affiliate has existed for fewer than twelve (12) months, Employee Count means the highest number of Employees at any time since formation. Employee Count is measured on the date You first make Production Use of the Licensed Work and again on the first day of each calendar quarter thereafter.

"For-Profit Entity" means a person or entity organized or operated primarily for commercial or financial gain. A nonprofit, charitable organization, educational institution, public research organization, public safety or public health organization, environmental protection organization, or government institution is not a For-Profit Entity solely because it receives funding, cost recovery, or fees related to its mission.

"Hosted" means making the Licensed Work, or a material portion of its functionality, available to third parties over a network as a managed, hosted, or software-as-a-service Product. Hosting or using the Licensed Work for internal purposes within an organization is not considered a Competitive Offering. Licensor considers your organization to include all of your Affiliates under Common Control. Professional services, consulting, training, integration, customization, or managed operations performed solely for a single customer's dedicated environment under that customer's control for that customer's internal business use are not, by themselves, a Competitive Offering.

"Product" means software, a service, or a combination thereof that is offered to end users to manage in their own environments or offered as a service on a Hosted basis.

"Production Use" means any use of the Licensed Work, other than development, testing, evaluation, or non-production staging, to support internal business operations or to provide products or services to third parties.

"You" means the individual or legal entity exercising rights under this License. "Your" has a corresponding meaning.

